# Who plays on 'Monday Night Football' tonight? Time, TV channel, schedule for NFL Week 6 games
       Jared Greenspan
      October 13, 2025  4:54 pm EDT                    Young quarterbacks take centerstage in another "Monday Night Football" doubleheader tonight.
The top two picks in last year's NFL Draft — Caleb Williams and Jayden Daniels — meet in the second game, as the [Bears](https://www.sportingnews.com/us/nfl/chicago-bears) visit the [Commanders](https://www.sportingnews.com/us/nfl/washington-commanders).
  
 [WATCH: Monday Night Football LIVE on the new ESPN app](https://go.web.plus.espn.com/c/2436205/535101/9070?subId1=sports&subId2=site-us-52b63b63a40bb8ca01986052)  
It's the second head-to-head meeting between the two phenoms, and we'll see how they can top last year's showdown, which was punctuated by a game-winning, 52-yard Hail Mary touchdown from Daniels as time expired.
In the first game, Michael Penix Jr. leads the [Falcons](https://www.sportingnews.com/us/nfl/atlanta-falcons) on the other side of their bye week to take on Josh Allen's [Bills](https://www.sportingnews.com/us/nfl/buffalo-bills). Buffalo is hoping to rebound from its first loss of the season and Allen's worst game of the year. 
The Sporting News has everything you need to know about watching "Monday Night Football" tonight, including TV and streaming information for both games. 
**LIVE: **[Follow Bills vs. Falcons updates from 'Monday Night Football'](https://www.sportingnews.com/us/nfl/news/bills-falcons-live-score-highlights-monday-night-football/6b72708d9dbdccd5fbb1d439)

## Who plays on Monday Night Football tonight? 


- **Matchups: **Falcons vs. Bills | Commanders vs. Bears

- **Locations: **Mercedes-Benz Stadium in Atlanta | Northwest Stadium in Landover, Maryland

The Falcons host the Bills on "Monday Night Football" from Mercedes-Benz Stadium in Atlanta, Georgia. 
Then, in the later game, the Commanders host the Bears at Northwest Stadium in Landover, Maryland.

## What time is the NFL game on tonight? 


- **Date: **Monday, Oct. 13

- **Time: **7:15 p.m. ET (Falcons vs. Bills) | 8:15 p.m. ET (Commanders vs. Bears)

Kickoff of Falcons vs. Bills is set for 7:15 p.m. ET on Monday, Oct. 13. Commanders vs. Bears will begin an hour later with kickoff scheduled for 8:15 p.m. ET.

## What channel is Monday Night Football on tonight? 


- **TV channel: **ABC | ESPN

- **Live stream: **[ESPN](https://go.web.plus.espn.com/c/2436205/535101/9070?subId1=sports&subId2=site-us-52b63b63a40bb8ca01986052) | [Fubo](https://www.fubo.tv/welcome/leagues/191277?irad=356362&irmp=2436205&subId1=nfleditorial&subId2=site-us-52b63b63a40bb8ca01986052)

Falcons vs. Bills will air live on ESPN with Chris Fowler (play-by-play), Dan Orlovsky (analyst), Louis Riddick (analyst), Katie George (reporter) and Peter Schrager (reporter) on the call.
ABC will carry a live broadcast of Commanders vs. Bears with Joe Buck (play-by-play), Troy Aikman (analyst), Lisa Salters (reporter) and Laura Rutledge (reporter) calling the game.
Viewers can stream both games on the brand new [ESPN](https://go.web.plus.espn.com/c/2436205/535101/9070?subId1=sports&subId2=site-us-52b63b63a40bb8ca01986052) app and [Fubo](https://www.fubo.tv/welcome/leagues/191277?irad=356362&irmp=2436205&subId1=nfleditorial&subId2=site-us-52b63b63a40bb8ca01986052), with the latter offering a free trial.

## Monday Night Football radio station


- **Radio channel: **[SiriusXM](https://www.siriusxm.com/campaigns/nfl?ab&promocode=TA1MOFREE&utm_campaign=Prosp_NA_BAU&utm_source=2025-09_NA_SXIRPLAT-1FORFREE-OFF-PHX-SPORTINGMEDIA&utm_medium=Affiliate&utm_content=Sporting%20Media&utm_term=site-us-52b63b63a40bb8ca01986052)

For the first game, fans can head to [SiriusXM](https://www.siriusxm.com/campaigns/nfl?ab&promocode=TA1MOFREE&utm_campaign=Prosp_NA_BAU&utm_source=2025-09_NA_SXIRPLAT-1FORFREE-OFF-PHX-SPORTINGMEDIA&utm_medium=Affiliate&utm_content=Sporting%20Media&utm_term=site-us-52b63b63a40bb8ca01986052) channel 88, NFL Radio, for the national broadcast. Team-specific calls are available on channel 225 (Bills broadcast) and 226 (Falcons broadcast). 
For the second game, the national call will be played on [SiriusXM](https://www.siriusxm.com/campaigns/nfl?ab&promocode=TA1MOFREE&utm_campaign=Prosp_NA_BAU&utm_source=2025-09_NA_SXIRPLAT-1FORFREE-OFF-PHX-SPORTINGMEDIA&utm_medium=Affiliate&utm_content=Sporting%20Media&utm_term=site-us-52b63b63a40bb8ca01986052) channel 230. Team-specific calls can be found on channel 227 (Bears broadcast) and 228 (Commanders broadcast).
